{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And in Holland, there were lots of very rich Jews, Dutch Jews-- not the German refugees, but the Dutch Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "There were many who were in the diamond industry and they had loads of money.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And there were many who were in stores and shops.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Some of the very biggest stores in Holland were owned by Jews, and they had lots of money, and they could afford to buy these visas.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It was interesting that the interviewer who interviewed me on this other program for this [INAUDIBLE] video, Mr.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], he, at that point in the interview, said his family also had a lot of those visas for Ecuador and all that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "So he must have been rich.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So those people who had these visas-- they also had the blue stamp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, some people sort of are very critical-- you know, why did the Germans allow all this kind of thing?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Basically, they wanted to get all their Germans back, and they were quite happy to give away Jews in order to get Germans back to their country.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was basically the plan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they could see that normally, no other country was going to take Jews just like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, an interesting thing was that there had been this conference in [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Evian ?] in 1938 where all the countries of the world assembled in [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Evian ?] on Lake Geneva to decide what to do about the Jewish problem in Germany and on the continent, and how they were going to help the refugees.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the outcome of it all was they all said, yes, we ought to help, but no single country offered take any of the refugees in.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And basically, that was the situation.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
